34/*
35 * sbix -- Standard Bitmap Graphics
36 * https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/sbix
37 * https://developer.apple.com/fonts/TrueType-Reference-Manual/RM06/Chap6sbix.html
38 */
39#define HB_OT_TAG_sbix HB_TAG('s','b','i','x')
40

42namespace OT {

44
45struct SBIXGlyph
46{
47 SBIXGlyph* copy (hb_serialize_context_t *c, unsigned int data_length) const
48 {
49 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
50 SBIXGlyph* new_glyph = c->start_embed<SBIXGlyph> ();
51 if (unlikely (!new_glyph)) return_trace (nullptr);
52 if (unlikely (!c->extend_min (new_glyph))) return_trace (nullptr);
53
54 new_glyph->xOffset = xOffset;
55 new_glyph->yOffset = yOffset;
56 new_glyph->graphicType = graphicType;
57 data.copy (c, count: data_length);
58 return_trace (new_glyph);
59 }
60
61 HBINT16 xOffset; /* The horizontal (x-axis) offset from the left
62 * edge of the graphic to the glyph’s origin.
63 * That is, the x-coordinate of the point on the
64 * baseline at the left edge of the glyph. */
65 HBINT16 yOffset; /* The vertical (y-axis) offset from the bottom
66 * edge of the graphic to the glyph’s origin.
67 * That is, the y-coordinate of the point on the
68 * baseline at the left edge of the glyph. */
69 Tag graphicType; /* Indicates the format of the embedded graphic
70 * data: one of 'jpg ', 'png ' or 'tiff', or the
71 * special format 'dupe'. */
72 UnsizedArrayOf<HBUINT8>
73 data; /* The actual embedded graphic data. The total
74 * length is inferred from sequential entries in
75 * the glyphDataOffsets array and the fixed size
76 * (8 bytes) of the preceding fields. */
77 public:
78 DEFINE_SIZE_ARRAY (8, data);
79};
80
81struct SBIXStrike
82{
83 static unsigned int get_size (unsigned num_glyphs)
84 { return min_size + num_glyphs * HBUINT32::static_size; }
85
86 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
87 {
88 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
89 return_trace (c->check_struct (this) &&
90 imageOffsetsZ.sanitize_shallow (c, c->get_num_glyphs () + 1));
91 }
92
93 hb_blob_t *get_glyph_blob (unsigned int glyph_id,
94 hb_blob_t *sbix_blob,
95 hb_tag_t file_type,
96 int *x_offset,
97 int *y_offset,
98 unsigned int num_glyphs,
99 unsigned int *strike_ppem) const
100 {
101 if (unlikely (!ppem)) return hb_blob_get_empty (); /* To get Null() object out of the way. */
102
103 unsigned int retry_count = 8;
104 unsigned int sbix_len = sbix_blob->length;
105 unsigned int strike_offset = (const char *) this - (const char *) sbix_blob->data;
106 assert (strike_offset < sbix_len);
107
108 retry:
109 if (unlikely (glyph_id >= num_glyphs ||
110 imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id + 1] <= imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id] ||
111 imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id + 1] - imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id] <= SBIXGlyph::min_size ||
112 (unsigned int) imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id + 1] > sbix_len - strike_offset))
113 return hb_blob_get_empty ();
114
115 unsigned int glyph_offset = strike_offset + (unsigned int) imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id] + SBIXGlyph::min_size;
116 unsigned int glyph_length = imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id + 1] - imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id] - SBIXGlyph::min_size;
117
118 const SBIXGlyph *glyph = &(this+imageOffsetsZ[glyph_id]);
119
120 if (glyph->graphicType == HB_TAG ('d','u','p','e'))
121 {
122 if (glyph_length >= 2)
123 {
124 glyph_id = *((HBUINT16 *) &glyph->data);
125 if (retry_count--)
126 goto retry;
127 }
128 return hb_blob_get_empty ();
129 }
130
131 if (unlikely (file_type != glyph->graphicType))
132 return hb_blob_get_empty ();
133
134 if (strike_ppem) *strike_ppem = ppem;
135 if (x_offset) *x_offset = glyph->xOffset;
136 if (y_offset) *y_offset = glyph->yOffset;
137 return hb_blob_create_sub_blob (parent: sbix_blob, offset: glyph_offset, length: glyph_length);
138 }
139
140 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c, unsigned int available_len) const
141 {
142 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
143 unsigned int num_output_glyphs = c->plan->num_output_glyphs ();
144
145 auto* out = c->serializer->start_embed<SBIXStrike> ();
146 if (unlikely (!out)) return_trace (false);
147 auto snap = c->serializer->snapshot ();
148 if (unlikely (!c->serializer->extend (out, num_output_glyphs + 1))) return_trace (false);
149 out->ppem = ppem;
150 out->resolution = resolution;
151 HBUINT32 head;
152 head = get_size (num_glyphs: num_output_glyphs + 1);
153
154 bool has_glyphs = false;
155 for (unsigned new_gid = 0; new_gid < num_output_glyphs; new_gid++)
156 {
157 hb_codepoint_t old_gid;
158 if (!c->plan->old_gid_for_new_gid (new_gid, old_gid: &old_gid) ||
159 unlikely (imageOffsetsZ[old_gid].is_null () ||
160 imageOffsetsZ[old_gid + 1].is_null () ||
161 imageOffsetsZ[old_gid + 1] <= imageOffsetsZ[old_gid] ||
162 imageOffsetsZ[old_gid + 1] - imageOffsetsZ[old_gid] <= SBIXGlyph::min_size) ||
163 (unsigned int) imageOffsetsZ[old_gid + 1] > available_len)
164 {
165 out->imageOffsetsZ[new_gid] = head;
166 continue;
167 }
168 has_glyphs = true;
169 unsigned int delta = imageOffsetsZ[old_gid + 1] - imageOffsetsZ[old_gid];
170 unsigned int glyph_data_length = delta - SBIXGlyph::min_size;
171 if (!(this+imageOffsetsZ[old_gid]).copy (c: c->serializer, data_length: glyph_data_length))
172 return_trace (false);
173 out->imageOffsetsZ[new_gid] = head;
174 head += delta;
175 }
176 if (has_glyphs)
177 out->imageOffsetsZ[num_output_glyphs] = head;
178 else
179 c->serializer->revert (snap);
180 return_trace (has_glyphs);
181 }
182
183 public:
184 HBUINT16 ppem; /* The PPEM size for which this strike was designed. */
185 HBUINT16 resolution; /* The device pixel density (in PPI) for which this
186 * strike was designed. (E.g., 96 PPI, 192 PPI.) */
187 protected:
188 UnsizedArrayOf<Offset32To<SBIXGlyph>>
189 imageOffsetsZ; /* Offset from the beginning of the strike data header
190 * to bitmap data for an individual glyph ID. */
191 public:
192 DEFINE_SIZE_ARRAY (4, imageOffsetsZ);
193};

195struct sbix
196{
197 static constexpr hb_tag_t tableTag = HB_OT_TAG_sbix;
198
199 bool has_data () const { return version; }
200
201 const SBIXStrike &get_strike (unsigned int i) const { return this+strikes[i]; }
202
203 struct accelerator_t
204 {
205 accelerator_t (hb_face_t *face)
206 {
207 table = hb_sanitize_context_t ().reference_table<sbix> (face);
208 num_glyphs = face->get_num_glyphs ();
209 }
210 ~accelerator_t () { table.destroy (); }
211
212 bool has_data () const { return table->has_data (); }
213
214 bool get_extents (hb_font_t *font,
215 hb_codepoint_t glyph,
216 hb_glyph_extents_t *extents,
217 bool scale = true) const
218 {
219 /* We only support PNG right now, and following function checks type. */
220 return get_png_extents (font, glyph, extents, scale);
221 }
222
223 hb_blob_t *reference_png (hb_font_t *font,
224 hb_codepoint_t glyph_id,
225 int *x_offset,
226 int *y_offset,
227 unsigned int *available_ppem) const
228 {
229 return choose_strike (font).get_glyph_blob (glyph_id, sbix_blob: table.get_blob (),
230 HB_TAG ('p','n','g',' '),
231 x_offset, y_offset,
232 num_glyphs, strike_ppem: available_ppem);
233 }
234
235 bool paint_glyph (hb_font_t *font, hb_codepoint_t glyph, hb_paint_funcs_t *funcs, void *data) const
236 {
237 if (!has_data ())
238 return false;
239
240 int x_offset = 0, y_offset = 0;
241 unsigned int strike_ppem = 0;
242 hb_blob_t *blob = reference_png (font, glyph_id: glyph, x_offset: &x_offset, y_offset: &y_offset, available_ppem: &strike_ppem);
243 hb_glyph_extents_t extents;
244 hb_glyph_extents_t pixel_extents;
245
246 if (blob == hb_blob_get_empty ())
247 return false;
248
249 if (!hb_font_get_glyph_extents (font, glyph, extents: &extents))
250 return false;
251
252 if (unlikely (!get_extents (font, glyph, &pixel_extents, false)))
253 return false;
254
255 bool ret = funcs->image (paint_data: data,
256 image: blob,
257 width: pixel_extents.width, height: -pixel_extents.height,
258 HB_PAINT_IMAGE_FORMAT_PNG,
259 slant: font->slant_xy,
260 extents: &extents);
261
262 hb_blob_destroy (blob);
263 return ret;
264 }
265
266 private:
267
268 const SBIXStrike &choose_strike (hb_font_t *font) const
269 {
270 unsigned count = table->strikes.len;
271 if (unlikely (!count))
272 return Null (SBIXStrike);
273
274 unsigned int requested_ppem = hb_max (font->x_ppem, font->y_ppem);
275 if (!requested_ppem)
276 requested_ppem = 1<<30; /* Choose largest strike. */
277 /* TODO Add DPI sensitivity as well? */
278 unsigned int best_i = 0;
279 unsigned int best_ppem = table->get_strike (i: 0).ppem;
280
281 for (unsigned int i = 1; i < count; i++)
282 {
283 unsigned int ppem = (table->get_strike (i)).ppem;
284 if ((requested_ppem <= ppem && ppem < best_ppem) ||
285 (requested_ppem > best_ppem && ppem > best_ppem))
286 {
287 best_i = i;
288 best_ppem = ppem;
289 }
290 }
291
292 return table->get_strike (i: best_i);
293 }
294
295 struct PNGHeader
296 {
297 HBUINT8 signature[8];
298 struct
299 {
300 struct
301 {
302 HBUINT32 length;
303 Tag type;
304 } header;
305 HBUINT32 width;
306 HBUINT32 height;
307 HBUINT8 bitDepth;
308 HBUINT8 colorType;
309 HBUINT8 compressionMethod;
310 HBUINT8 filterMethod;
311 HBUINT8 interlaceMethod;
312 } IHDR;
313
314 public:
315 DEFINE_SIZE_STATIC (29);
316 };
317
318 bool get_png_extents (hb_font_t *font,
319 hb_codepoint_t glyph,
320 hb_glyph_extents_t *extents,
321 bool scale = true) const
322 {
323 /* Following code is safe to call even without data.
324 * But faster to short-circuit. */
325 if (!has_data ())
326 return false;
327
328 int x_offset = 0, y_offset = 0;
329 unsigned int strike_ppem = 0;
330 hb_blob_t *blob = reference_png (font, glyph_id: glyph, x_offset: &x_offset, y_offset: &y_offset, available_ppem: &strike_ppem);
331
332 const PNGHeader &png = *blob->as<PNGHeader>();
333
334 if (png.IHDR.height >= 65536 || png.IHDR.width >= 65536)
335 {
336 hb_blob_destroy (blob);
337 return false;
338 }
339
340 extents->x_bearing = x_offset;
341 extents->y_bearing = png.IHDR.height + y_offset;
342 extents->width = png.IHDR.width;
343 extents->height = -1 * png.IHDR.height;
344
345 /* Convert to font units. */
346 if (strike_ppem && scale)
347 {
348 float scale = font->face->get_upem () / (float) strike_ppem;
349 extents->x_bearing = roundf (extents->x_bearing * scale);
350 extents->y_bearing = roundf (extents->y_bearing * scale);
351 extents->width = roundf (extents->width * scale);
352 extents->height = roundf (extents->height * scale);
353 }
354
355 if (scale)
356 font->scale_glyph_extents (extents);
357
358 hb_blob_destroy (blob);
359
360 return strike_ppem;
361 }
362
363 private:
364 hb_blob_ptr_t<sbix> table;
365
366 unsigned int num_glyphs;
367 };
368
369 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
370 {
371 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
372 return_trace (likely (c->check_struct (this) &&
373 version >= 1 &&
374 strikes.sanitize (c, this)));
375 }
376
377 bool
378 add_strike (hb_subset_context_t *c, unsigned i) const
379 {
380 if (strikes[i].is_null () || c->source_blob->length < (unsigned) strikes[i])
381 return false;
382
383 return (this+strikes[i]).subset (c, available_len: c->source_blob->length - (unsigned) strikes[i]);
384 }
385
386 bool serialize_strike_offsets (hb_subset_context_t *c) const
387 {
388 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
389
390 auto *out = c->serializer->start_embed<Array32OfOffset32To<SBIXStrike>> ();
391 if (unlikely (!out)) return_trace (false);
392 if (unlikely (!c->serializer->extend_min (out))) return_trace (false);
393
394 hb_vector_t<Offset32To<SBIXStrike>*> new_strikes;
395 hb_vector_t<hb_serialize_context_t::objidx_t> objidxs;
396 for (int i = strikes.len - 1; i >= 0; --i)
397 {
398 auto* o = out->serialize_append (c: c->serializer);
399 if (unlikely (!o)) return_trace (false);
400 *o = 0;
401 auto snap = c->serializer->snapshot ();
402 c->serializer->push ();
403 bool ret = add_strike (c, i);
404 if (!ret)
405 {
406 c->serializer->pop_discard ();
407 out->pop ();
408 c->serializer->revert (snap);
409 }
410 else
411 {
412 objidxs.push (v: c->serializer->pop_pack ());
413 new_strikes.push (v&: o);
414 }
415 }
416 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < new_strikes.length; ++i)
417 c->serializer->add_link (ofs&: *new_strikes[i], objidx: objidxs[new_strikes.length - 1 - i]);
418
419 return_trace (true);
420 }
421
422 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t* c) const
423 {
424 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
425
426 sbix *sbix_prime = c->serializer->start_embed<sbix> ();
427 if (unlikely (!sbix_prime)) return_trace (false);
428 if (unlikely (!c->serializer->embed (this->version))) return_trace (false);
429 if (unlikely (!c->serializer->embed (this->flags))) return_trace (false);
430
431 return_trace (serialize_strike_offsets (c));
432 }
433
434 protected:
435 HBUINT16 version; /* Table version number — set to 1 */
436 HBUINT16 flags; /* Bit 0: Set to 1. Bit 1: Draw outlines.
437 * Bits 2 to 15: reserved (set to 0). */
438 Array32OfOffset32To<SBIXStrike>
439 strikes; /* Offsets from the beginning of the 'sbix'
440 * table to data for each individual bitmap strike. */
441 public:
442 DEFINE_SIZE_ARRAY (8, strikes);
443};
444
445struct sbix_accelerator_t : sbix::accelerator_t {
446 sbix_accelerator_t (hb_face_t *face) : sbix::accelerator_t (face) {}
447};
